        • [ - ] blackbird - member since 18-Aug-18

          @realnews He was actually fine, just not as flamboyant as people expect him to be. Mbappe "changed the game" because he could offer the link-up and good communication with Neymar that the more inexperienced players couldn't in the first half, but that doesn't mean Neymar played poorly. There's no point in finding and exploiting space if the players around you never take advantage of your good positioning. Also, an attacker can't do much if the midfield keeps losing the ball to the opponents and most of the first-half action wound up with PSG defenders desperately trying to fend of Guingamp around their own (PSG's) goal. Please don't make the Argentina mistake of blaming lackluster team performance on one of the best players. Actually the impression you have of Mbappe and Neymar is a perfect example of how having good teammate support allows a player to shine (Mbappe with Neymar in 2nd half), but not having that support limits you (Neymar w/o Mbappe in 1st half). Team sport!
